                            <comment id="14638185" author="srowen" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 05:36:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems very related to, or almost a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9180&quot; title=&quot;Accept --name option in spark-submit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-9180&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-9180&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14638187" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 05:43:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh it is. I missed it. So spark-shell is fixed. Then should I fix pyspark in this jira?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14638319" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 06:52:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sowen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sowen&quot;&gt;sowen&lt;/a&gt;, I just tested &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9180&quot; title=&quot;Accept --name option in spark-submit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-9180&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-9180&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; now. even with it, &lt;tt&gt;spark.app.name&lt;/tt&gt; is still ignored in spark-shell although it can be set via &lt;tt&gt;--name&lt;/tt&gt; option. Ideally, it would be nice all the shells work in the same manner. I summarized the behaviors of all 4 shells in the description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14638325" author="srowen" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 06:54:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah there&apos;s probably an additional change to be made, just have a look at what was done in that PR to propose something consistent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
